  {
    "id": "f_csv_8762f53aa3",
    "slug": "the-millions-of-human-beings-who-were-shot-tortured-starved-treated-like-anim",
    "texto": "The millions of human beings who were shot, tortured, starved, treated like animals and made the object of a conspiracy of ridicule, can sleep in peace in their communal graves, for at least the struggle in which they died has enabled their descendants, isolated in their air-conditioned apartments, to believe, on the strength of their daily dose of television, that they are happy and free. The Communards went down, fighting to the last, so that you too could qualify for a Caribbean cruise.",
    "autor": "Raoul Vaneigem",
    "autorSlug": "raoul-vaneigem",
    "explicacao": "Metáfora atribuída a Raoul Vaneigem: compara elementos do cotidiano para falar de temas ligados a felicidade. O trecho “The millions of human beings who were shot, tortured, starved, treated like animals and made the …” usa imagem concreta para lembrar que felicidade, anarchism, politics pedem movimento e interpretação pessoal, em tom de termino e politics.",
    "semantica": {
      "categoriaPrincipal": "felicidade",
